description: All riders will ride on the Kreitler Headwind Roller System for 2 miles competing for the fastest elapsed time in their category.  Riders will ride in the approximate order of registration.  USCF rules apply and helmets are required.

notes: No rerides.  An Iowa Roller Champion will be awarded for each category.  Your 3 best times averaged is your state championship time.  There will also be a prize drawing for a set of Kreitler roller at this race.  To be eligible you must compete in at least 4 of the 8 roller races in 2012.  Each race entry is a drawing entry (after 4 races)

title: Race Like A Girl
description: Track-style racing. Each rider does 3 races: scratch race, points race, and miss and out. Categories are Men\'s A, Men\'s B, Women\'s A, Women\'s B. Juniors can race any category based on skill and strength. Also have a kid\' race (helmets and registration required). This is a laid-back, family friendly race designed to encourage new racers, particularly women racers, to get involved in the sport.
course: 0.4 mile loop at Union Park. Closed Course. Mostly flat except for one small rise about 3/4 thru each lap.
registration: $10 per night for men, $5 per night for women, juniors and kids FREE. Unlicensed riders will need to also purchase a $10 USA Cycling one-day license.
notes: No prize money will be given, only \"schwag\"
directions: Located just east of Pennsylvania Ave and north of E. Jefferson. Union Park upper loop (not the carousel loop). Des Moines, Iowa.

title: Clear Lake Family Fun Ride
flyer_url: Clear Lake Family Fun Rides updated 52312.pdf
description:
The new “Bike and Hike” option is a ride that follows the trails around Clear Lake’s shoreline. Pit stops include Macintosh Woods State Park, Sisters’ Prairie Bike Trail, and Clear Lake State Park.  There will be drawings at each stop for t-shirts, water bottles, ice cream and more!
    Farm-to-farm / local foods ride
    The 50-mile ride to Meservey, Alexander, Sheffield, and Thornton has a return route that swings through Ventura and then wraps around Clear Lake, ending at City Park.
    The final ride option is a 85-mile route that passes through Ventura, Meservey, Alexander, Sheffield, and Thornton, ending back in Clear Lake.  It too ends at City Park.

title: Capitol City Cross

address.street: Stone Park - E. Fulton Dr & SE 3th Street

description:
Capital City Cross is a two day event!
Plan a weekend of cyclocross fun! Come out and enjoy this new spectator-friendly venue only minutes from downtown Des Moines. Last year was a BLAST!
course:
This race is SUPER SPECTATOR Friendly!!
If you have never been to a cyclocross race, you are missing out! There is action everywhere and you can watch the race from several vantage points! Kick back for an afternoon and watch cyclocross! Bring lawn chairs and park yourself, or check out the whole course.
registration: Register online via USA Cycling or Day of race.
notes:
Parking
There is plenty of parking off SE Fulton Drive. Some parking available at Community Center on East Side and then the side streets.

Post-Race Party
After the races, we will have a social gathering. Venue to be posted soon. We\'ll be doing what most cyclocross racers and fans do after a race - sharing war stories! All are invited. It\'ll be fun!

From out of town?
You are so close to downtown Des Moines where there are plenty of great restaurants and hotels to spend the weekend. In fact, many of us plan to grab a bite to eat after Saturday\'s race. Everyone is welcome to join us!
directions:
Venue Directions
From I-235

    Get off on 3rd Street.
    Go south through downtown Des Moines.
    3rd turns into SQ 3rd and merges with
    SW 2nd near Principal Park (IA Cubs baseball field)
    Continue on SW 2nd and take a left on E. Fulton Drive.
    Go less than 2 blocks and the street ends at Stone Park

title: Spooky Cross
description: Spooky Cross is back for another year but under new management. We are hoping to not disappoint in what has always been a classis location on the calendar and a favorite of the locals. It will be the same great location, and we hope that we can make it better, but the bar has been set high in past years.
course: Course will be a classic style cross course designed by the same guy who designs the Lions Park course. He is known for creating challenging courses that still retain a good flow through out.
registration: <p>Day of registration will open at 9:00 AM and will close 15mins prior to the beginning of each race.</p><p>Racer\'s will be using same number both days.</p>
notes:
Women may enter any men’s race for which they are eligible by age, category, and any performance requirements. They may also enter categorized races for men that are up to one category lower than their women\'s category. For road, track, and cyclo-cross events, category 1 women may enter men’s races up to two categories lower. In addition, master women may compete in men’s masters races, subject to other eligibility requirements, as follows: category 1 and 2 master women may enter men’s events for riders up to 10 years above their racing ages; category 3 and 4 master women may enter men’s events for riders up to 20 years above their racing ages.

In the event of low rider turnout, the organizers reserve the right to cancel/combine events and prize lists as necessary or to award prizes to only the top half of each category.
directions:
Driving Directions from I-80/I-235
1. Head north on I-35 N
2. Take exit 126 for Douglas Ave toward Urbandale
3. Turn left at Douglas Ave
4. Continue on Douglas Pkwy
5. Look for a sign on the left (south) side of the street 
where you’ll enter a large field and drive to the south 
towards the start/finish
